g.text: Maintain a vector of shapes, and each shape points to an array
of instance data vector. The instance data vector contains information
about each instance of the shape it belongs to
When we need to render multiple shape instance, we issue a vkCmdDraw() with
multiple instance count as parameter. This means we have a separate draw
call for each shape. So if vkCmdDraw() is treated as a basis operation
then complexity is directly proportional to number of shapes
IT IS NOT POSSIBLE TO RENDER DIFFERENT SHAPES
but at the least, we're able to reduce the number of drqw calls
All instance data will be sent as
vertex buffer and will be recreated
